1
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:34,918
=Vanished Name=

2
00:01:35,224 --> 00:01:37,784
=Episode 22=
(Secret Romance)

3
00:01:38,572 --> 00:01:39,212
Be careful.

4
00:01:50,492 --> 00:01:51,332
You're a runner, huh?

5
00:01:54,412 --> 00:01:55,864
Check out my mobile castle.

6
00:01:56,692 --> 00:01:58,692
Isn't it like Optimus Prime
from Transformers?

7
00:02:02,692 --> 00:02:03,371
It can transform.

8
00:02:05,612 --> 00:02:06,291
Take a look?

9
00:02:07,256 --> 00:02:07,772
Okay.

10
00:02:07,772 --> 00:02:08,571
Come on.

11
00:02:12,531 --> 00:02:13,172
Be careful.

12
00:02:15,971 --> 00:02:16,612
Be careful.

13
00:02:30,251 --> 00:02:31,971
Your presence
really lights up the place.

14
00:02:33,732 --> 00:02:36,091
Look at my setup.
It's as good as a Rolls-Royce.

15
00:02:36,411 --> 00:02:37,411
I've got everything.

16
00:02:37,411 --> 00:02:39,212
I cook with this rice cooker.

17
00:02:39,256 --> 00:02:41,052
I have warm food wherever I go.

18
00:02:41,332 --> 00:02:42,251
Sunflower seeds.

19
00:02:42,531 --> 00:02:43,192
Have some.

20
00:02:43,851 --> 00:02:45,452
So you sleep here?

21
00:02:46,091 --> 00:02:47,651
Yeah, when I'm out on the road.

22
00:02:48,371 --> 00:02:49,651
T-This is all dirty.

23
00:02:49,651 --> 00:02:51,651
I'll get you new ones, brand new.

24
00:02:52,172 --> 00:02:52,728
No need.

25
00:02:53,016 --> 00:02:55,571
You don't need to come with me.

26
00:02:56,052 --> 00:02:57,172
The road is tough.

27
00:02:57,691 --> 00:02:58,732
Stay at a guesthouse.

28
00:02:59,571 --> 00:03:00,251
No need.

29
00:03:01,811 --> 00:03:02,332
Listen.

30
00:03:03,052 --> 00:03:05,571
You will be my driving master

31
00:03:06,691 --> 00:03:07,411
from now on.

32
00:03:08,251 --> 00:03:09,612
I-I'll be your master?

33
00:03:11,371 --> 00:03:11,892
Master.

34
00:03:14,612 --> 00:03:17,452
Alright, I'm a master now.

35
00:03:20,292 --> 00:03:20,888
Let's go.

36
00:03:22,371 --> 00:03:22,892
No, we can't.

37
00:03:23,411 --> 00:03:23,932
Why not?

38
00:03:24,492 --> 00:03:25,971
It would be drunk driving.

39
00:03:26,651 --> 00:03:28,632
Well, since I'm your master now,

40
00:03:29,251 --> 00:03:30,452
here's your first lesson.

41
00:03:31,452 --> 00:03:33,052
Drink if you drive.

42
00:03:35,371 --> 00:03:35,892
Say it.

43
00:03:36,651 --> 00:03:39,251
You mean, "Don't drink if you drive."

44
00:03:40,531 --> 00:03:44,728
Ren Xiaoming, stop running like a thief.

45
00:03:45,172 --> 00:03:48,052
The upright citizens
might tackle you to the ground.

46
00:03:48,571 --> 00:03:50,932
Stop following me.
We won't see each other again.

47
00:03:51,411 --> 00:03:52,851
So you do feel ashamed?

48
00:03:53,371 --> 00:03:56,411
Why didn't you think twice
when you caused a scene yesterday?

49
00:03:56,531 --> 00:03:58,971
Shut up.
Bring it up again, and we're through.

50
00:03:59,172 --> 00:04:01,892
Sure, just tell me
how your mom punished you.

51
00:04:02,292 --> 00:04:04,732
You were so bold yesterday,
calling her names.

52
00:04:06,932 --> 00:04:07,971
Why are you pinching me?

53
00:04:07,971 --> 00:04:09,612
You asked how my mom punished me.

54
00:04:10,172 --> 00:04:11,332
Firsthand experience.

55
00:04:11,332 --> 00:04:13,012
Totally firsthand. Ouch.

56
00:04:13,851 --> 00:04:15,651
You're biting the hand that feeds you.

57
00:04:15,851 --> 00:04:17,331
I saved your skin yesterday.

58
00:04:18,092 --> 00:04:20,371
Every question your mom asked
was a trick question.

59
00:04:20,612 --> 00:04:23,451
Luckily I was quick-witted,
or she would've skinned us both alive.

60
00:04:23,612 --> 00:04:26,584
Quick-witted? You were a bootlicker.

61
00:04:26,852 --> 00:04:29,211
What's the point
of fighting with my mother-in-law?

62
00:04:29,571 --> 00:04:33,451
I can go full throttle
to be the best bootlicker.

63
00:04:34,612 --> 00:04:36,571
Who's your mother-in-law? Huh?

64
00:04:36,771 --> 00:04:37,691
Shameless.

65
00:04:38,612 --> 00:04:40,451
If you listen to her,
why do you see me off?

66
00:04:40,532 --> 00:04:41,532
Who? Me?

67
00:04:42,092 --> 00:04:43,131
I'm not seeing you off.

68
00:04:43,972 --> 00:04:45,292
You're just lying.

69
00:04:45,811 --> 00:04:48,292
She didn't forbid me
from taking the train.

70
00:04:50,492 --> 00:04:51,192
Where you going?

71
00:04:51,412 --> 00:04:53,811
Why do you care
where a shameless guy is going?

72
00:04:53,932 --> 00:04:54,811
Stop snooping.

73
00:04:56,691 --> 00:04:58,932
I'm going to see my girlfriend.

74
00:04:58,932 --> 00:05:00,972
She is really lonely in the big city.

75
00:05:01,011 --> 00:05:01,880
I'll stay with her.

76
00:05:05,811 --> 00:05:06,852
Really?

77
00:05:09,592 --> 00:05:10,131
Come here.

78
00:05:10,571 --> 00:05:11,211
What?

79
00:05:11,211 --> 00:05:12,331
Show me the ticket.

80
00:05:12,331 --> 00:05:14,811
You're digging in my pocket in public?

81
00:05:15,131 --> 00:05:16,331
Give it to me.

82
00:05:20,011 --> 00:05:20,612
Same as usual.

83
00:05:20,952 --> 00:05:22,732
Take the sleeper berth.
I'll take your seat.

84
00:05:22,732 --> 00:05:23,811
No, we sleep together.

85
00:05:25,652 --> 00:05:27,011
You said it yourself.

86
00:05:28,211 --> 00:05:29,251
What are you thinking?

87
00:05:46,492 --> 00:05:48,052
Wrong way to crack sunflower seeds.

88
00:05:48,251 --> 00:05:48,932
Spit it out.

89
00:05:50,932 --> 00:05:51,932
That's the way to do it.

90
00:05:52,451 --> 00:05:53,016
Try it.

91
00:05:57,331 --> 00:05:58,092
There you go.

92
00:06:13,492 --> 00:06:16,052
This city is at least
five times bigger than Qidaohezi.

93
00:06:17,371 --> 00:06:20,932
Economics says population
is the lifeblood of a city.

94
00:06:21,172 --> 00:06:24,732
More people, more dividends,
and more chances to survive.

95
00:06:24,771 --> 00:06:29,331
Fewer people mean slower development
and fewer people to sustain.

96
00:06:30,172 --> 00:06:33,720
So, population and the economy
are positively correlated variables.

97
00:06:34,211 --> 00:06:35,451
What are you looking at?

98
00:06:36,371 --> 00:06:39,960
I've always said
you're the smartest person I know.

99
00:06:40,371 --> 00:06:42,211
How do I have such good taste?

100
00:06:44,891 --> 00:06:45,412
Thirsty?

101
00:06:58,052 --> 00:06:59,732
When did you decide to come to Qingzhou?

102
00:07:01,571 --> 00:07:02,211
Not telling you.

103
00:07:02,811 --> 00:07:04,344
Come on, tell me.

104
00:07:06,891 --> 00:07:09,811
The day you told me
you were going on a blind date.

105
00:07:10,412 --> 00:07:13,011
That early? And you told me just now?

106
00:07:13,652 --> 00:07:14,808
You sure can keep a secret.

107
00:07:20,612 --> 00:07:22,052
But what about your mom?

108
00:07:25,891 --> 00:07:29,732
My dad said he would
stop drinking and beating her.

109
00:07:30,331 --> 00:07:31,492
He'd be his former self.

110
00:07:32,732 --> 00:07:33,811
He treated my mom okay.

111
00:07:39,131 --> 00:07:40,972
What if we break up someday?

112
00:07:42,092 --> 00:07:43,771
Would you regret coming with me?

113
00:07:44,932 --> 00:07:45,691
No way.

114
00:07:46,652 --> 00:07:48,292
If we break up, it'll be me dumping you.

115
00:07:48,691 --> 00:07:50,652
Who'd have regrets
when they have someone new?

116
00:07:52,172 --> 00:07:53,451
Are you a dog or something?

117
00:07:54,211 --> 00:07:55,972
Feels good. Come on, harder.

118
00:07:56,052 --> 00:07:56,771
Feels good.

119
00:08:05,852 --> 00:08:06,532
Bai Shu.

120
00:08:07,771 --> 00:08:08,891
She's on the road

121
00:08:09,492 --> 00:08:10,492
with Zhang Fang.

122
00:08:10,691 --> 00:08:12,972
Let's send her a photo, too. Come on.

123
00:08:16,691 --> 00:08:17,211
Wait.

124
00:08:20,331 --> 00:08:22,172
We're in Qingzhou.

125
00:08:27,732 --> 00:08:28,312
Zhang Fang.

126
00:08:29,371 --> 00:08:30,532
Do you have any wishes?

127
00:08:32,292 --> 00:08:32,892
No.

128
00:08:33,451 --> 00:08:34,892
All my wishes have come true.

129
00:09:23,292 --> 00:09:24,731
Shouldn't I help you find a place?

130
00:09:25,132 --> 00:09:27,932
No need.
Don't you trust my survival skills?

131
00:09:29,652 --> 00:09:31,012
I just wanted to

132
00:09:31,211 --> 00:09:32,372
vet the options for you.

133
00:09:33,012 --> 00:09:34,372
I have a great taste.

134
00:09:34,772 --> 00:09:37,372
Don't worry.
I'll find myself a decent place.

135
00:09:37,532 --> 00:09:40,571
Go back to school.
You have class tomorrow.

136
00:09:41,292 --> 00:09:42,331
Are you sure?

137
00:09:42,571 --> 00:09:44,012
Yeah, I got this. Just go.

138
00:09:47,851 --> 00:09:48,772
Go back to school.

139
00:09:49,731 --> 00:09:50,731
These aren't heavy.

140
00:09:52,091 --> 00:09:53,412
Text me once you settle in.

141
00:09:55,252 --> 00:09:55,851
I'm off.

142
00:09:56,132 --> 00:09:56,652
Go.

143
00:09:59,064 --> 00:09:59,611
Bye.

144
00:10:09,932 --> 00:10:10,611
Go.

145
00:10:21,611 --> 00:10:24,691
This is the central area of Qingzhou,
surrounded by tall buildings.

146
00:10:25,331 --> 00:10:26,811
A quiet spot amidst the bustle.

147
00:10:27,052 --> 00:10:27,608
Yeah.

148
00:10:27,971 --> 00:10:30,571
This used to be part of
the civil defense project.

149
00:10:30,932 --> 00:10:32,172
Atomic bomb-proof.

150
00:10:41,132 --> 00:10:42,571
It may be semi-underground

151
00:10:42,772 --> 00:10:45,211
but the lighting is amazing here.

152
00:10:46,132 --> 00:10:49,292
The people who lived here
all "got high".

153
00:10:51,052 --> 00:10:52,691
They moved to high-rises.

154
00:10:54,571 --> 00:10:55,292
Lucky place, huh?

155
00:10:55,971 --> 00:10:58,252
Yeah, if you rent it now,

156
00:10:58,252 --> 00:11:00,331
I'll throw in a Simmons bed...

157
00:11:01,451 --> 00:11:02,012
mattress.

158
00:11:17,851 --> 00:11:18,372
Hello?

159
00:11:18,652 --> 00:11:20,052
How's it going? Found a place?

160
00:11:20,811 --> 00:11:22,971
Yeah, it's awesome.

161
00:11:25,172 --> 00:11:26,211
Where is it?

162
00:11:26,611 --> 00:11:31,331
Prime location.
High safety rating. Plenty of space.

163
00:11:33,012 --> 00:11:34,652
Privacy protection is top-notch.

164
00:11:35,451 --> 00:11:37,772
Really? How much is the rent?

165
00:11:38,292 --> 00:11:39,451
So stingy.

166
00:11:39,932 --> 00:11:43,012
I'm in Qingzhou now.
Shouldn't I enjoy myself?

167
00:11:44,172 --> 00:11:45,491
Alright, send me the address.

168
00:11:46,052 --> 00:11:48,611
I have some extra daily supplies.
I'll bring them over.

169
00:11:49,052 --> 00:11:50,892
You're giving me your extras?

170
00:11:51,252 --> 00:11:53,091
They're below me. Keep them yourself.

171
00:11:53,412 --> 00:11:54,200
Don't come.

172
00:11:54,772 --> 00:11:58,532
We'll be alone in one room,
with just one bed.

173
00:11:59,172 --> 00:12:00,211
Come if you want.

174
00:12:00,331 --> 00:12:03,372
Stop talking nonsense,
or I'll rip your mouth.

175
00:12:04,052 --> 00:12:05,491
I don't even care to visit.

176
00:12:06,292 --> 00:12:08,772
(Library)
Come out. Dinner's on me.

177
00:12:09,412 --> 00:12:11,412
How can I let you pay?

178
00:12:12,372 --> 00:12:13,532
What do you want for dinner?

179
00:12:14,012 --> 00:12:15,372
I'll improve your diet.

180
00:12:16,412 --> 00:12:16,971
Fine.

181
00:12:18,331 --> 00:12:19,892
I know an awesome place.

182
00:12:20,132 --> 00:12:20,731
Let's go there.

183
00:12:21,172 --> 00:12:22,252
Okay, see you soon.

184
00:12:36,052 --> 00:12:38,292
Here? What's there to eat?

185
00:12:38,292 --> 00:12:38,932
You hick.

186
00:12:39,292 --> 00:12:40,892
There are all kinds of food.

187
00:12:41,132 --> 00:12:43,652
They have barbecue and everything.

188
00:12:43,892 --> 00:12:44,811
And simple meals.

189
00:12:45,412 --> 00:12:47,691
No simple meals.
Let me buy you a pork knuckle.

190
00:12:47,731 --> 00:12:49,851
I don't want pork knuckle.

191
00:12:49,851 --> 00:12:51,571
Who comes here for pork knuckles?

192
00:12:51,571 --> 00:12:53,211
I want steak.

193
00:12:53,211 --> 00:12:54,264
(Specialty 198 yuan)

194
00:12:55,372 --> 00:12:58,211
(Hand-cut steak)
Looks delicious. I saw it last time.

195
00:12:58,211 --> 00:13:00,491
It's too expensive.
I wanted to try it with you.

196
00:13:00,971 --> 00:13:03,292
(Steak doneness chart)
I'll get one for share.

197
00:13:03,491 --> 00:13:04,451
This is raw.

198
00:13:04,652 --> 00:13:06,611
Don't be ridiculous. It says well done.

199
00:13:06,611 --> 00:13:08,091
Are you living under a rock?

200
00:13:08,532 --> 00:13:09,052
Here.

201
00:13:10,211 --> 00:13:13,611
It's a set meal.
Steak plus salad plus fruit wine.

202
00:13:14,052 --> 00:13:16,052
Choose one you like.

203
00:13:16,451 --> 00:13:18,091
Whatever. Let's have steak.

204
00:13:18,372 --> 00:13:20,331
We are having steak. Pick something.

205
00:13:20,331 --> 00:13:21,652
Order one and we'll share.

206
00:13:22,292 --> 00:13:24,052
What's the point? Order two.

207
00:13:24,451 --> 00:13:26,491
I don't want two servings. Just one.

208
00:13:27,532 --> 00:13:29,132
Since when are you rich?

209
00:13:30,091 --> 00:13:30,971
How much do you have?

210
00:13:31,372 --> 00:13:34,052
Why would I tell you? You might rob me.

211
00:13:35,012 --> 00:13:35,851
You're loaded, huh?

212
00:13:35,851 --> 00:13:36,652
I won't tell you.

213
00:13:37,211 --> 00:13:39,451
Then I won't hold back. Five portions.

214
00:13:41,571 --> 00:13:42,971
Don't listen to her. Just two.

215
00:13:43,532 --> 00:13:45,052
Hello, we have sets of 198,

216
00:13:45,052 --> 00:13:46,132
218, 238,

217
00:13:46,172 --> 00:13:47,052
258, 288,

218
00:13:47,172 --> 00:13:48,252
298, and 318 yuan.

219
00:13:48,252 --> 00:13:49,451
Which one would you like?

220
00:13:49,772 --> 00:13:50,971
So many eights?

221
00:13:51,412 --> 00:13:52,372
Two 318 sets.

222
00:13:52,491 --> 00:13:53,652
Okay, two orders of 318.

223
00:13:53,652 --> 00:13:55,096
We have vegetable and chicken salad,

224
00:13:55,096 --> 00:13:56,731
costing 68, 89, or 108 yuan.

225
00:13:56,851 --> 00:13:58,611
They pair best with steak.

226
00:13:58,851 --> 00:14:00,451
This chicken salad is fine.

227
00:14:00,451 --> 00:14:01,132
No.

228
00:14:01,372 --> 00:14:02,052
Pork knuckle.

229
00:14:02,052 --> 00:14:03,331
- No...
- I like pork knuckle.

230
00:14:03,331 --> 00:14:04,571
- Come on...
- I love pork knuckle.

231
00:14:04,652 --> 00:14:06,412
I love it.

232
00:14:06,932 --> 00:14:08,856
Sure, let's go eat pork knuckle.

233
00:14:11,932 --> 00:14:12,731
Full?

234
00:14:13,211 --> 00:14:15,288
About to burst.

235
00:14:17,731 --> 00:14:19,292
Alright, I won't walk you further.

236
00:14:19,412 --> 00:14:20,252
Head back to school.

237
00:14:23,491 --> 00:14:24,932
My turn to watch you go.

238
00:14:25,611 --> 00:14:27,331
Why? You go first.

239
00:14:27,331 --> 00:14:27,864
No.

240
00:14:29,731 --> 00:14:32,571
Fine, I paid for the meal.

241
00:14:32,691 --> 00:14:33,691
How about a kiss?

242
00:14:35,611 --> 00:14:37,372
What? Are you mad?

243
00:14:37,451 --> 00:14:39,772
So many people. No kissing.

244
00:14:44,611 --> 00:14:46,292
You kissed me? A payback.

245
00:14:47,292 --> 00:14:47,892
I'm off.

246
00:15:15,811 --> 00:15:17,892
Are you there yet, babe?

247
00:15:49,091 --> 00:15:49,691
Who is it?

248
00:15:53,372 --> 00:15:54,172
Who is it?

249
00:16:03,012 --> 00:16:04,091
What's wrong with you?

250
00:16:04,091 --> 00:16:05,292
- You followed me?
- Prime location.

251
00:16:07,172 --> 00:16:09,052
Close to the Earth's core.
Obviously prime.

252
00:16:09,132 --> 00:16:10,052
High safety rating.

253
00:16:10,892 --> 00:16:12,611
The landlord says
it's atomic bomb-proof.

254
00:16:12,772 --> 00:16:14,172
The public area is huge, huh?

255
00:16:14,571 --> 00:16:16,932
There are people chatting and drinking.

256
00:16:17,211 --> 00:16:18,851
You're a liar.

257
00:16:19,252 --> 00:16:20,052
Liar.

258
00:16:20,052 --> 00:16:22,532
Keep it down. I'm trying to sleep here.

259
00:16:24,211 --> 00:16:27,292
See, a friendly reminder for the noise.

260
00:16:27,532 --> 00:16:30,132
I didn't lie. Privacy is well-protected.

261
00:16:30,571 --> 00:16:32,052
Change your perspective.

262
00:16:36,491 --> 00:16:38,372
And life can be better.

263
00:16:38,571 --> 00:16:39,091
Look.

264
00:16:41,532 --> 00:16:42,892
Feel the breeze.

265
00:16:44,772 --> 00:16:48,292
This is a rat hole.
You can't live here. Let's go.

266
00:16:48,892 --> 00:16:49,451
Let's go.

267
00:16:49,451 --> 00:16:51,412
No, it's the cheapest place.

268
00:16:52,571 --> 00:16:53,331
Are you broke?

269
00:16:53,944 --> 00:16:54,571
I have money.

270
00:16:55,491 --> 00:16:57,211
It's not about money.
I want to live here.

271
00:16:57,211 --> 00:16:58,211
Can you stay out of it?

272
00:16:58,532 --> 00:16:59,992
You paid for dinner and a taxi,

273
00:16:59,992 --> 00:17:01,172
but you live here.

274
00:17:01,611 --> 00:17:02,971
It upsets me.

275
00:17:02,971 --> 00:17:05,092
What kind of person do you think I am?

276
00:17:05,932 --> 00:17:07,011
This is temporary.

277
00:17:07,011 --> 00:17:09,291
Once I get a job and earn money,
I'll move, all right?

278
00:17:10,172 --> 00:17:12,172
You said there are plenty
of opportunities here.

279
00:17:12,372 --> 00:17:13,652
Don't you have faith in me?

280
00:17:13,652 --> 00:17:15,932
I don't want you to suffer for me here.

281
00:17:16,251 --> 00:17:18,172
I didn't come to Qingzhou for you.

282
00:17:19,251 --> 00:17:20,971
That was just a side reason.

283
00:17:20,971 --> 00:17:23,011
I also see the great potential
of this place.

284
00:17:23,451 --> 00:17:25,172
I want to start a business here.

285
00:17:25,372 --> 00:17:27,652
My life is about to take off here.

286
00:17:32,251 --> 00:17:33,412
That's enough.

287
00:17:43,372 --> 00:17:44,092
Look outside.

288
00:17:46,892 --> 00:17:48,211
The view's not bad, huh?

289
00:17:48,612 --> 00:17:50,852
I don't care.
Move out once you earn money.

290
00:17:51,892 --> 00:17:53,731
Okay, that's for sure.

291
00:18:02,971 --> 00:18:04,531
This room is rented out?

292
00:18:07,412 --> 00:18:08,652
I used to live here.

293
00:18:08,852 --> 00:18:10,771
See that? I put it there.

294
00:18:11,412 --> 00:18:12,932
Very artistic, right?

295
00:18:13,051 --> 00:18:14,251
Now I live here.

296
00:18:14,971 --> 00:18:17,172
I moved to the high-rise opposite.

297
00:18:21,172 --> 00:18:22,412
I have a girlfriend.

298
00:18:27,412 --> 00:18:30,372
Buddy, soundproofing isn't great here.

299
00:18:30,372 --> 00:18:31,652
Just so you know.

300
00:18:32,892 --> 00:18:34,852
Alright, enjoy your stay here.

301
00:18:34,971 --> 00:18:36,652
Good luck to you guys. Bye.

302
00:18:37,691 --> 00:18:38,291
I'm off.

303
00:18:42,092 --> 00:18:43,572
Why did he mention the soundproofing?

304
00:18:46,051 --> 00:18:47,412
I'll tell you later.

305
00:18:52,892 --> 00:18:56,412
My mom always told me
that smart people shop at flea markets.

306
00:18:57,531 --> 00:19:00,332
Back when she steamed buns,
new equipment cost two grand,

307
00:19:00,652 --> 00:19:03,092
but only resold for a few hundred.
What a ripoff.

308
00:19:04,132 --> 00:19:05,531
We've got brains.

309
00:19:05,932 --> 00:19:07,531
Of course we won't make a losing deal.

310
00:19:07,531 --> 00:19:08,892
Yeah, you're the smartest.

311
00:19:09,051 --> 00:19:10,051
Get a rice cooker.

312
00:19:10,612 --> 00:19:11,932
Can I help you?

313
00:19:14,092 --> 00:19:16,172
Get a small one for the two of us.

314
00:19:16,332 --> 00:19:16,852
This one?

315
00:19:18,291 --> 00:19:20,051
This will work. How much is it?

316
00:19:20,291 --> 00:19:20,812
230 yuan.

317
00:19:20,932 --> 00:19:21,491
How much?

318
00:19:21,491 --> 00:19:22,040
230 yuan.

319
00:19:22,412 --> 00:19:23,051
Original price?

320
00:19:23,051 --> 00:19:24,691
It's used. How much is it now?

321
00:19:25,211 --> 00:19:26,104
That's the price.

322
00:19:26,172 --> 00:19:26,776
Twenty.

323
00:19:27,291 --> 00:19:28,332
That's way too cheap.

324
00:19:28,491 --> 00:19:29,240
Forget it then.

325
00:19:29,491 --> 00:19:31,211
Fine, take it.

326
00:19:31,731 --> 00:19:32,531
First deal today.

327
00:19:33,291 --> 00:19:34,360
Got anything else here?

328
00:19:35,051 --> 00:19:36,652
Fans and small appliances.

329
00:19:38,451 --> 00:19:39,771
Let's get you a fan.

330
00:19:40,691 --> 00:19:42,612
Isn't your little rat hole stuffy?

331
00:19:42,612 --> 00:19:43,731
It's super stuffy.

332
00:19:45,011 --> 00:19:45,691
How much is it?

333
00:19:45,691 --> 00:19:46,251
500 yuan.

334
00:19:46,491 --> 00:19:48,120
That's the original price?

335
00:19:48,251 --> 00:19:49,412
This is second-hand.

336
00:19:49,731 --> 00:19:51,160
It's good stuff back in the day.

337
00:19:51,160 --> 00:19:51,691
How much now?

338
00:19:52,852 --> 00:19:54,332
The lowest I can offer is 150.

339
00:19:56,971 --> 00:19:57,652
How much is it?

340
00:19:58,092 --> 00:19:59,332
This one is 300.

341
00:20:00,491 --> 00:20:01,172
Three hundred?

342
00:20:02,211 --> 00:20:03,132
Does it even work?

343
00:20:03,132 --> 00:20:03,852
Yeah.

344
00:20:03,852 --> 00:20:04,572
Show me.

345
00:20:05,372 --> 00:20:07,291
It's older than both of us.

346
00:20:08,531 --> 00:20:09,691
I'll explain later.

347
00:20:09,892 --> 00:20:11,372
Give me 300, and I'll blow air.

348
00:20:12,172 --> 00:20:13,491
24 hour nonstop.

349
00:20:16,412 --> 00:20:16,932
Working?

350
00:20:17,011 --> 00:20:17,531
Yeah.

351
00:20:19,572 --> 00:20:20,332
The switch works?

352
00:20:20,612 --> 00:20:21,172
Yeah.

353
00:20:22,852 --> 00:20:23,960
Give me a better price.

354
00:20:24,932 --> 00:20:25,572
Come on.

355
00:20:25,971 --> 00:20:26,852
Your offer?

356
00:20:29,011 --> 00:20:29,572
Two fifty.

357
00:20:30,332 --> 00:20:31,852
Are you calling me an idiot?

358
00:20:31,852 --> 00:20:33,531
I'm also buying your rice cooker.

359
00:20:33,612 --> 00:20:34,691
Just a bit more.

360
00:20:34,771 --> 00:20:36,211
That's already too much.

361
00:20:36,852 --> 00:20:37,372
Five more.

362
00:20:38,971 --> 00:20:39,691
Deal.

363
00:20:43,051 --> 00:20:45,491
- Two seventy-five, right?
- Yeah.

364
00:20:45,491 --> 00:20:46,172
Two seventy-five.

365
00:20:46,652 --> 00:20:47,572
Count it.

366
00:20:48,291 --> 00:20:49,016
Correct, huh?

367
00:20:49,491 --> 00:20:50,092
Thanks, sir.

368
00:20:50,572 --> 00:20:51,412
Come back anytime.

369
00:20:51,576 --> 00:20:52,092
Alright.

370
00:20:53,332 --> 00:20:55,352
That guy knows nothing.

371
00:20:55,352 --> 00:20:56,971
That's why he sold it to me so cheap.

372
00:20:57,731 --> 00:21:00,892
This thing's an antique.
It's worth a fortune, you know?

373
00:21:01,211 --> 00:21:03,051
Getting it for 250 is a steal.

374
00:21:03,572 --> 00:21:04,824
A steal? Really?

375
00:21:04,824 --> 00:21:06,251
Of course. What do you know?

376
00:21:06,612 --> 00:21:09,132
This is cheap? You're such a fool.

377
00:21:09,531 --> 00:21:10,932
You're the fool here.

378
00:21:11,332 --> 00:21:12,211
So ignorant.

379
00:21:13,092 --> 00:21:15,771
Since when are you into antiques?
Who taught you?

380
00:21:18,251 --> 00:21:19,731
That blind date.

381
00:21:20,531 --> 00:21:21,291
So cute.

382
00:21:23,531 --> 00:21:24,932
What's your name?

383
00:21:26,412 --> 00:21:28,451
I'll name you Harry doll.

384
00:21:30,011 --> 00:21:33,251
He's really something.
Great family background.

385
00:21:33,531 --> 00:21:34,812
He knows how to save money.

386
00:21:34,812 --> 00:21:36,332
He's the one who took me there.

387
00:21:36,731 --> 00:21:38,531
He said you can find treasures there.

388
00:21:42,932 --> 00:21:43,691
What are you doing?

389
00:21:44,211 --> 00:21:45,731
Why'd you leave my fan there?

390
00:21:46,412 --> 00:21:48,971
I'm weak as a kitten. I can't carry it.

391
00:21:49,132 --> 00:21:50,771
Call that guy here to carry it.

392
00:22:00,372 --> 00:22:01,092
Are you jealous?

393
00:22:01,251 --> 00:22:02,011
Get lost.

394
00:22:02,011 --> 00:22:02,731
Are you jealous?

395
00:22:02,731 --> 00:22:03,892
Get lost.

396
00:22:04,092 --> 00:22:06,200
He likes my friend.

397
00:22:06,200 --> 00:22:07,572
He's not interested in me.

398
00:22:08,372 --> 00:22:09,612
Why wouldn't he be?

399
00:22:09,691 --> 00:22:11,451
I'd say you're way out of his league.

400
00:22:11,612 --> 00:22:12,372
Oh, please.

401
00:22:12,372 --> 00:22:15,771
I'm just some country bumpkin to him.

402
00:22:16,132 --> 00:22:17,172
What do you mean?

403
00:22:17,612 --> 00:22:19,332
We may be from the countryside,

404
00:22:19,332 --> 00:22:21,080
but we're not country bumpkins.

405
00:22:22,332 --> 00:22:23,051
Where's the pot?

406
00:22:24,892 --> 00:22:27,771
I'm counting on it
to get us a new place in Qingzhou.

407
00:22:31,771 --> 00:22:32,572
How much is the fan?

408
00:22:34,771 --> 00:22:35,932
You know about antiques too?

409
00:22:36,132 --> 00:22:37,451
This is mine. Not for sale.

410
00:22:37,812 --> 00:22:38,852
I saw it first.

411
00:22:39,172 --> 00:22:40,691
She's the boss. I listen to her.

412
00:22:53,932 --> 00:22:55,172
(Qingzhou, 2023)
Liu Xiaoran's lawyer

413
00:22:55,412 --> 00:22:58,372
gave me the bank statements
for your joint account last month.

414
00:22:58,771 --> 00:23:00,051
Can you explain to me?

415
00:23:00,291 --> 00:23:03,051
Why did you buy two apartments
in Qidaohezi last month?

416
00:23:03,291 --> 00:23:05,771
And savings insurance
for your mom and your brother.

417
00:23:07,092 --> 00:23:08,691
And a burial plot at Wuming Mountain.

418
00:23:09,011 --> 00:23:12,892
Got any coffee here?
I've been so tired lately.

419
00:23:13,332 --> 00:23:14,456
Don't change the subject.

420
00:23:14,812 --> 00:23:16,372
These large expenditures

421
00:23:16,572 --> 00:23:19,612
will make the court think
you're transferring assets on purpose.

422
00:23:21,892 --> 00:23:23,812
That money is what I deserved.

423
00:23:24,771 --> 00:23:26,812
I've been handling his PR work
all these years.

424
00:23:27,291 --> 00:23:29,011
And I've been playing along.

425
00:23:29,852 --> 00:23:31,251
Why can't I spend my own money?

426
00:23:31,572 --> 00:23:33,051
Can't you just wait?

427
00:23:33,291 --> 00:23:37,048
Wait until after the divorce.
Then you can buy whatever you want.

428
00:23:37,291 --> 00:23:38,332
I may not have time.

429
00:23:39,092 --> 00:23:40,652
What's the rush now?

430
00:23:56,531 --> 00:23:58,372
(Every fact has its visible side.)

431
00:24:00,011 --> 00:24:02,691
(But it also has a hidden side,
the dark side of the moon.)

432
00:24:04,664 --> 00:24:06,872
(Qingzhou, 2008)

433
00:24:23,224 --> 00:24:27,160
(Professional Logistics,
Trustworthy Delivery)

434
00:24:27,932 --> 00:24:30,892
(He Yuqiong didn't have much luck
finding a job in Qingzhou.)

435
00:24:31,771 --> 00:24:35,812
(No diploma for office work.
No experience in sales.)

436
00:24:36,211 --> 00:24:40,172
(In the end, he found a job
as a loader at a delivery station.)

437
00:24:41,132 --> 00:24:43,572
(He had to unload
tons of packages every day,)

438
00:24:44,251 --> 00:24:46,291
(sometimes all night long.)

439
00:24:53,691 --> 00:24:56,291
I'll give you a back rub.
Tell me if it's too hard or too soft.

440
00:24:56,572 --> 00:24:58,892
(Xiaofei needed monthly treatments.)

441
00:24:59,491 --> 00:25:03,251
(Business at the bathhouse was slow,
not even five jobs a day.)

442
00:25:04,491 --> 00:25:08,092
(After the new semester started,
I stopped asking for money.)

443
00:25:10,051 --> 00:25:10,731
Coming.

444
00:25:11,892 --> 00:25:12,491
Thank you.

445
00:25:13,572 --> 00:25:14,412
Waitress.

446
00:25:16,051 --> 00:25:17,852
We've ordered. Serve the dishes now.

447
00:25:18,291 --> 00:25:19,332
Extra spicy and numbing.

448
00:25:19,332 --> 00:25:20,531
Okay, got it. Noted.

449
00:25:20,531 --> 00:25:21,731
Be faster.

450
00:25:32,652 --> 00:25:33,932
(After the night shifts,)

451
00:25:33,932 --> 00:25:34,691
(Axiang Noodles)

452
00:25:34,691 --> 00:25:38,051
(we'd meet at the noodle stall
under the overpass for breakfast.)

453
00:25:38,852 --> 00:25:39,812
Ma'am.

454
00:25:41,652 --> 00:25:43,011
- Morning.
- Two noodles.

455
00:25:43,612 --> 00:25:44,291
Two, huh?

456
00:25:44,291 --> 00:25:45,291
Yeah, the usual.

457
00:25:46,092 --> 00:25:46,691
Here we are.

458
00:25:46,691 --> 00:25:47,852
Two noodles, same as always.

459
00:25:54,892 --> 00:25:56,211
Here we go.

460
00:25:59,491 --> 00:26:00,412
Enjoy.

461
00:26:00,971 --> 00:26:02,051
Shout if you need anything.

462
00:26:02,251 --> 00:26:02,852
Okay.

463
00:26:14,932 --> 00:26:16,412
I've made enough for the remote.

464
00:26:17,291 --> 00:26:17,971
Have a drumstick.

465
00:26:18,652 --> 00:26:19,572
(I've also been busy.)

466
00:26:20,332 --> 00:26:23,051
(I promised to buy a big flat-screen TV
for the New Year.)

467
00:26:24,051 --> 00:26:25,852
(Now I saved up enough for the remote.)

468
00:26:39,572 --> 00:26:42,451
(I can endure any hardship
as long as it pays.)

469
00:26:43,332 --> 00:26:46,731
(To work hard, you have to be tough
and endure anything.)

470
00:26:47,771 --> 00:26:50,332
(Of course, there were times
I couldn't take it.)

471
00:26:51,332 --> 00:26:52,531
A top university student?

472
00:26:53,211 --> 00:26:55,572
You tutored my daughter for a month.

473
00:26:55,771 --> 00:26:58,652
Her grades didn't improve,
and they actually dropped.

474
00:26:59,812 --> 00:27:02,451
Ma'am, please don't fire me.

475
00:27:03,572 --> 00:27:06,971
I-I need to support my mom and brother.

476
00:27:07,132 --> 00:27:08,132
How is that my problem?

477
00:27:10,332 --> 00:27:11,612
Ma'am, please.

478
00:27:11,892 --> 00:27:13,011
I'm begging you.

479
00:27:13,011 --> 00:27:14,132
What are you doing?

480
00:27:14,132 --> 00:27:15,291
Get up. What are you doing?

481
00:27:15,291 --> 00:27:16,051
Please.

482
00:27:16,531 --> 00:27:18,612
- I have to support my mom.
- Get up.

483
00:27:18,612 --> 00:27:20,451
I'll pay you the full amount, okay?

484
00:27:20,691 --> 00:27:21,731
Full amount. There.

485
00:27:22,616 --> 00:27:23,251
Okay.

486
00:27:41,211 --> 00:27:41,932
Put this on.

487
00:27:41,932 --> 00:27:42,691
What is this?

488
00:27:42,691 --> 00:27:44,531
Your little flower.

489
00:27:44,932 --> 00:27:46,132
Couple's edition, huh?

490
00:27:47,691 --> 00:27:49,652
There are a lot of leftovers today.

491
00:27:49,892 --> 00:27:50,612
What's there?

492
00:27:50,852 --> 00:27:52,491
There's beef, which you love.

493
00:27:52,491 --> 00:27:55,372
Then let's have a happy little hotpot.

494
00:27:57,932 --> 00:27:58,691
See?

495
00:27:59,172 --> 00:28:00,531
Isn't the rice cooker useful?

496
00:28:00,652 --> 00:28:02,251
Way better than the induction cooker

497
00:28:02,332 --> 00:28:04,011
that trips the breaker all the time.

498
00:28:04,372 --> 00:28:05,971
Look, stick a chopstick here.

499
00:28:07,051 --> 00:28:09,051
It doesn't trip. So convenient.

500
00:28:09,211 --> 00:28:10,372
You're the expert.

501
00:28:13,771 --> 00:28:17,172
You're still missing a desk here.

502
00:28:18,572 --> 00:28:21,132
Where would we put it?
There's no room anywhere.

503
00:28:24,412 --> 00:28:26,971
Why is it so hard for us to get a desk?

504
00:28:29,892 --> 00:28:31,211
You want a desk?

505
00:28:32,372 --> 00:28:33,771
When I was little,

506
00:28:34,491 --> 00:28:37,172
I had to do homework
on the dining table or the windowsill.

507
00:28:37,612 --> 00:28:39,291
I thought to myself, when I grow up,

508
00:28:39,572 --> 00:28:41,051
I must have my own desk.

509
00:28:41,332 --> 00:28:42,872
I'll keep it spotlessly clean,

510
00:28:43,032 --> 00:28:44,412
without any water or oil on it.

511
00:28:46,172 --> 00:28:47,491
Alright, noted.

512
00:28:49,336 --> 00:28:53,720
(Qingzhou, 2023)

513
00:29:04,612 --> 00:29:05,211
What's wrong?

514
00:29:05,971 --> 00:29:06,812
Nothing.

515
00:29:08,172 --> 00:29:09,332
Don't play games with me.

516
00:29:10,451 --> 00:29:12,051
I have no curiosity about you now.

517
00:29:12,892 --> 00:29:16,971
I found a lot of old photos
while tidying up at home today.

518
00:29:17,332 --> 00:29:19,652
Many of them are memories
from our time in the US.

519
00:29:22,971 --> 00:29:27,011
We used to bike together
to enjoy the spring scenery

520
00:29:28,812 --> 00:29:30,451
and watch the waterbirds migrate.

521
00:29:32,251 --> 00:29:33,251
In winter,

522
00:29:34,771 --> 00:29:37,011
we'd snuggle on the sofa at home,

523
00:29:38,251 --> 00:29:43,211
eating tacos and watching old movies.

524
00:29:46,211 --> 00:29:47,691
Over and over again.

525
00:29:50,172 --> 00:29:52,531
Those times were really good.

526
00:29:54,332 --> 00:29:56,812
I wasn't born with nostalgia.

527
00:29:57,612 --> 00:30:00,092
Maybe I once had it in me,
but it's gone now.

528
00:30:01,612 --> 00:30:03,011
I only look forward.

529
00:30:08,291 --> 00:30:10,491
You're someone who values

530
00:30:11,491 --> 00:30:12,892
and cherishes the past.

531
00:30:15,491 --> 00:30:17,172
I remember one year in the US,

532
00:30:17,412 --> 00:30:20,092
I gave you a pair of socks
for Christmas.

533
00:30:21,011 --> 00:30:23,211
You wore them for years
until they got a hole.

534
00:30:24,731 --> 00:30:26,691
You patched it up with a little flower.

535
00:30:28,251 --> 00:30:30,892
You said you'd keep them
even if you didn't wear them.

536
00:30:32,971 --> 00:30:34,132
And that fan,

537
00:30:35,572 --> 00:30:37,491
you brought it from China to the US.

538
00:30:38,211 --> 00:30:40,892
It sat in that run-down dorm room
the university assigned us.

539
00:30:42,092 --> 00:30:46,372
Then it followed us back
to this big apartment.

540
00:30:49,172 --> 00:30:50,522
You couldn't bear to throw away

541
00:30:51,416 --> 00:30:55,172
a pair of worn-out socks
and a ten-year-old fan.

542
00:30:59,892 --> 00:31:03,051
How can you let go
of ten years of our relationship?

543
00:31:06,731 --> 00:31:08,932
All relationships start out beautiful.

544
00:31:09,932 --> 00:31:11,531
As they say in the movies,

545
00:31:12,011 --> 00:31:13,208
you can guess the beginning,

546
00:31:14,572 --> 00:31:15,932
but you can't guess the ending.

547
00:31:16,971 --> 00:31:18,612
Because we never know

548
00:31:19,332 --> 00:31:22,211
what we'll go through

549
00:31:23,451 --> 00:31:24,691
or who we'll become.

550
00:31:25,971 --> 00:31:27,531
So we should remember the good times.

551
00:31:28,332 --> 00:31:29,531
At least when we look back,

552
00:31:30,491 --> 00:31:33,852
we'll still think well of each other.
That's all that matters.

553
00:31:43,412 --> 00:31:44,451
Well said.

554
00:31:49,372 --> 00:31:50,531
Very well said.

555
00:31:51,652 --> 00:31:54,132
I've hired the best lawyers in China.

556
00:31:55,491 --> 00:31:59,172
Liang Yi is just a small fry
in front of them.

557
00:32:02,412 --> 00:32:03,971
I'm winning this case.

558
00:32:28,852 --> 00:32:31,011
(All beginnings are beautiful.)

559
00:32:32,451 --> 00:32:35,251
(But not all beautiful things
should begin.)

560
00:32:36,691 --> 00:32:40,024
Today, on behalf of my client,
Mr. Liu Xiaoran,

561
00:32:40,152 --> 00:32:44,251
I'd like to make some objections
to the property division details

562
00:32:44,531 --> 00:32:45,691
you provided.

563
00:32:46,372 --> 00:32:50,172
First, we believe the car
currently driven by Ms. Ren Xiaoming

564
00:32:50,771 --> 00:32:52,691
should be removed from the list.

565
00:32:54,412 --> 00:32:56,251
This car was a Christmas gift

566
00:32:56,412 --> 00:33:00,332
given by Mr. Liu Xiaoran
to Ms. Ren Xiaoming in 2021.

567
00:33:00,612 --> 00:33:02,584
Gifts within marriage
do not need to be returned.

568
00:33:02,731 --> 00:33:04,051
Ms. Ren may have misunderstood.

569
00:33:04,531 --> 00:33:08,451
This car was purchased with funds
from Mr. Liu Xiaoran's company,

570
00:33:08,572 --> 00:33:11,211
assigned to Ms. Ren Xiaoming
as a company vehicle.

571
00:33:11,771 --> 00:33:13,531
It remains a company car.

572
00:33:14,051 --> 00:33:16,491
If Ms. Ren can provide written evidence

573
00:33:17,132 --> 00:33:20,291
proving Mr. Liu Xiaoran
formally gifted it,

574
00:33:20,771 --> 00:33:22,731
then you can certainly keep the car.

575
00:33:26,491 --> 00:33:27,092
Forget it.

576
00:33:30,051 --> 00:33:31,011
We're not divorced yet.

577
00:33:31,011 --> 00:33:32,172
Thanks.

578
00:33:34,092 --> 00:33:36,291
Additionally, similar to the car,

579
00:33:36,451 --> 00:33:39,132
over a dozen bags
and some luxury watches

580
00:33:39,531 --> 00:33:41,771
were purchased by the company

581
00:33:41,971 --> 00:33:44,172
for Ms. Ren to attend business events.

582
00:33:44,731 --> 00:33:45,971
Here's the list.

583
00:33:55,251 --> 00:33:56,412
Just cross them off.

584
00:33:57,211 --> 00:33:59,051
Anyway, I never liked these things.

585
00:34:00,491 --> 00:34:04,612
Also, there's a set
of antique English teaware,

586
00:34:05,092 --> 00:34:08,292
won at the Chinese Hong Kong
Spring Auction in 2015 for 180,000 HKD.

587
00:34:11,096 --> 00:34:12,632
(A set of antique English teaware)

588
00:34:12,732 --> 00:34:14,451
You even want this back too?

589
00:34:28,091 --> 00:34:28,852
Let's take a break.

590
00:34:44,852 --> 00:34:47,932
You gave up the car, bags, and watches,

591
00:34:48,131 --> 00:34:49,852
but you're crying over some cups?

592
00:34:50,332 --> 00:34:51,372
That's pathetic.

593
00:34:51,692 --> 00:34:54,611
Teaware, not cups. How's that pathetic?

594
00:34:55,412 --> 00:34:58,091
Say the word.
I'll get it back if you like it.

595
00:34:58,212 --> 00:34:59,571
I don't like it.

596
00:35:00,571 --> 00:35:01,571
What's going on?

597
00:35:07,732 --> 00:35:10,372
That year, he had just started writing.

598
00:35:10,651 --> 00:35:12,491
I was taking care of him.

599
00:35:13,171 --> 00:35:16,571
I proofread his work,
and ran to publishers, and printers.

600
00:35:17,332 --> 00:35:20,332
Finally, we earned our first million.

601
00:35:21,171 --> 00:35:23,651
We thought about taking a trip.

602
00:35:24,451 --> 00:35:25,752
So we went to Hong Kong, China.

603
00:35:26,372 --> 00:35:28,412
We happened to catch the Spring Auction.

604
00:35:29,732 --> 00:35:31,131
He said

605
00:35:31,971 --> 00:35:35,451
he'd buy something I like
to thank me for my hard work,

606
00:35:36,088 --> 00:35:38,531
no matter the cost.

607
00:35:39,372 --> 00:35:40,131
That's the one.

608
00:35:43,372 --> 00:35:48,451
That tea set was the cheapest item
at the auction.

609
00:35:50,971 --> 00:35:54,011
It's too cheap. I really don't like it.

610
00:35:55,372 --> 00:35:55,971
Forget it.

611
00:36:01,372 --> 00:36:04,611
(Some things are expensive
but worthless.)

612
00:36:05,372 --> 00:36:08,888
(Some things cost nothing
but hold eternal value.)

613
00:36:09,510 --> 00:36:12,696
(Semi-basement rental room,
Qingzhou, 2008)

614
00:36:15,091 --> 00:36:16,892
I brought food.

615
00:36:21,571 --> 00:36:22,732
What are you doing?

616
00:36:22,852 --> 00:36:24,091
Setting up a desk for you.

617
00:36:24,212 --> 00:36:27,852
From now on,
you can do homework at this desk.

618
00:36:29,651 --> 00:36:32,932
Nice, we don't have to
eat off a cardboard box anymore.

619
00:36:34,171 --> 00:36:36,412
Don't you dare eat at the desk.

620
00:36:36,692 --> 00:36:39,332
Listen, this desk
belongs to my girlfriend.

621
00:36:39,451 --> 00:36:43,651
She wants it spotless.
No water or oil on it.

622
00:36:43,932 --> 00:36:47,571
No one touches it, not even me.
It's hers alone.

623
00:36:47,932 --> 00:36:49,812
Your girlfriend is so picky.

624
00:36:50,292 --> 00:36:52,772
Dump her and be with me instead.

625
00:36:52,932 --> 00:36:54,451
I adore her.

626
00:36:54,531 --> 00:36:56,491
Maybe in your next life.

627
00:36:59,372 --> 00:37:00,611
Alright, take a break.

628
00:37:01,252 --> 00:37:01,892
Let's eat first.

629
00:37:08,372 --> 00:37:10,252
Hurry up. It'll get cold.

630
00:37:13,051 --> 00:37:13,772
Wash your hands.

631
00:37:14,772 --> 00:37:16,332
Why bother? I'm not done yet.

632
00:37:30,131 --> 00:37:31,252
Get another one.

633
00:37:31,692 --> 00:37:33,372
It's fine. Three-second rule.

634
00:38:06,372 --> 00:38:07,292
What's so funny?

635
00:38:12,091 --> 00:38:14,491
I finally have a desk of my own.

636
00:38:15,491 --> 00:38:17,011
What else do you want?

637
00:38:17,571 --> 00:38:18,692
Plenty more.

638
00:38:23,451 --> 00:38:24,372
Let me hear it.

639
00:38:26,292 --> 00:38:27,451
I want a bed.

640
00:38:28,292 --> 00:38:28,892
Here.

641
00:38:28,892 --> 00:38:30,772
Not like this.

642
00:38:31,692 --> 00:38:32,732
Not a sofa.

643
00:38:33,252 --> 00:38:34,852
Not a bunk bed like in the dorms.

644
00:38:34,852 --> 00:38:37,212
The kind that's huge and soft.

645
00:38:37,212 --> 00:38:41,292
One that feels like lying on a cloud.

646
00:38:42,131 --> 00:38:43,451
I also want a wardrobe.

647
00:38:44,171 --> 00:38:45,571
A really big one.

648
00:38:46,332 --> 00:38:48,171
So I can buy lots of stuff.

649
00:38:48,292 --> 00:38:49,732
Nobody touches it without my say-so.

650
00:38:51,651 --> 00:38:52,171
Okay.

651
00:38:59,651 --> 00:39:00,571
It's good to have you.

652
00:39:01,372 --> 00:39:03,892
I'm no longer
just one of 20 million in Qingzhou.

653
00:39:06,252 --> 00:39:07,571
Then what are you now?

654
00:39:08,451 --> 00:39:15,051
You and I together make two out of

655
00:39:17,651 --> 00:39:18,212
20 million.

656
00:39:18,571 --> 00:39:20,131
You sound pretty dumb.

657
00:39:20,451 --> 00:39:23,812
Two out of twenty million
is one out of ten million.

658
00:39:24,131 --> 00:39:26,372
A college student doesn't know math
as well as I do?

659
00:39:27,412 --> 00:39:29,451
Would it kill you
to be a little romantic?

660
00:39:35,571 --> 00:39:36,372
What?

661
00:39:44,051 --> 00:39:46,571
Seriously? Why's it losing color?

662
00:39:47,732 --> 00:39:48,692
It's on you, too.

663
00:39:53,292 --> 00:39:54,692
Are you silly?

664
00:39:55,332 --> 00:39:57,491
You rub it on your face
when you know it loses color?

665
00:39:58,011 --> 00:40:00,892
Good buddies share weal and woe.

666
00:40:00,892 --> 00:40:01,971
Who's your buddy?

667
00:40:05,292 --> 00:40:06,372
What are you doing?

668
00:40:06,451 --> 00:40:09,011
Stop moving. You'll ruin my desk.

669
00:40:10,971 --> 00:40:13,212
Wiping it with my towel? Give it back.

670
00:40:16,932 --> 00:40:17,651
Use this.

671
00:40:31,812 --> 00:40:32,651
You fool.

672
00:40:43,412 --> 00:40:44,692
Almost there.

673
00:40:45,091 --> 00:40:46,332
I can't walk anymore.

674
00:40:47,491 --> 00:40:48,372
I can't walk anymore.

675
00:40:49,051 --> 00:40:50,051
How much further?

676
00:40:50,772 --> 00:40:52,252
We're almost there.

677
00:40:52,376 --> 00:40:53,400
You've been

678
00:40:53,400 --> 00:40:54,932
saying that the whole way. Liar.

679
00:40:57,496 --> 00:40:58,852
I can't walk anymore.

680
00:40:59,892 --> 00:41:00,651
I'm done.

681
00:41:02,692 --> 00:41:04,692
My feet hurt.

682
00:41:05,571 --> 00:41:06,712
- I'm done.
- Ren Xiaoming.

683
00:41:07,732 --> 00:41:08,292
Ren Xiaoming.

684
00:41:10,812 --> 00:41:11,412
Ren Xiaoming.

685
00:41:11,412 --> 00:41:12,011
What?

686
00:41:12,171 --> 00:41:13,560
Does it remind you of something?

687
00:41:14,971 --> 00:41:15,772
What?

688
00:41:18,651 --> 00:41:22,131
Ren Xiaoming, run a bit further ahead...

689
00:41:22,651 --> 00:41:24,971
You can move up 20 spots in the grade.

690
00:41:25,131 --> 00:41:26,072
Get lost.

691
00:41:26,168 --> 00:41:28,011
Are you walking a dog?

692
00:41:30,772 --> 00:41:33,531
Walk to me, and you'll move up 50 spots.

693
00:41:33,531 --> 00:41:34,840
Stop running.

694
00:41:35,292 --> 00:41:36,332
Ren Xiaoming.

695
00:41:39,412 --> 00:41:40,212
Walk here,

696
00:41:40,812 --> 00:41:43,732
and you'll get
into a top or key university.

697
00:41:44,011 --> 00:41:45,852
You got into Qingzhou University.

698
00:41:46,292 --> 00:41:47,252
- Hurry up.
- I'm done.

699
00:41:47,892 --> 00:41:48,491
I'm not moving.

700
00:41:50,232 --> 00:41:50,808
Come on.

701
00:41:52,252 --> 00:41:52,772
Come on.

702
00:41:55,332 --> 00:41:57,892
You're about to
break into the top hundred.

703
00:42:42,852 --> 00:42:45,292
Xiaoming, where were you last night?

704
00:42:45,491 --> 00:42:48,292
Why didn't you answer your phone?

705
00:42:48,451 --> 00:42:49,732
We were so worried.

706
00:42:50,292 --> 00:42:51,091
Yeah.

707
00:42:51,611 --> 00:42:53,212
My student has an exam coming up.

708
00:42:53,212 --> 00:42:54,531
Her mom wanted me to tutor her.

709
00:42:55,011 --> 00:42:56,932
It got too late, so I stayed over.

710
00:42:57,491 --> 00:42:59,852
Xiaoming, go collect your money.

711
00:43:00,531 --> 00:43:01,131
What money?

712
00:43:01,332 --> 00:43:02,091
Your scholarship.

713
00:43:02,212 --> 00:43:03,131
Xiaomi.

714
00:43:05,000 --> 00:43:12,808
=Vanished Name=
